args:
The party manages to stop the Holywyrm,
but when battle begins to collapse the Sacred
Tree, they are split up. Audric then takes Phares
himself, and realizes that the man's true form
is that of the Progenitor.
Ever since we returned, you've been\nperceiving enemy attacks far too quickly\nto be using your eyes.
You see the truth of me, Ilia. I believe\nthis to be an effect of the pact.
I don't know if my body can't keep up with\nBahamut's power, or if it's merely a price I\nhad to pay to make it manifest.
But if my sight is the cost, I will\nconsider it a light price indeed.

In truth, I see better this way than I ever
did with my eyes. My senses are being
honed like the edge of a butcher's razor.
It is almost...frightening.
This power is great enough that I fear it\nmay slip from my grasp at any time...
But regrets? No. Right now, I just want to\nstay focused on what is to come.
Then we can start by taking down the\nchump in front of us!
Come, everyone! We are close now!
We managed to stop his movements.
Zethia was wielding a portion of\nBahamut's power, and her body was\nprobably at its limit.

Yes. But if my physical strength recovers,
I should be able to borrow that power
again. ...Ah, and my sight has returned
as well.
I think the black mana is causing the\nSacred Tree to collapse!
We have to climb down! Now!
Brother, I wonder if I might take my leave\nand visit the empty prince.
Of course. What are you planning?
I want to ask him something. I want to\nknow his mind when faced with the truth.
We gotta help everyone who fell!\nC'mon! DO SOMETHING ALREADY!
Calm yourself, Notte. We will make our\nway back down—carefully—and reunite\nwith them on one of the lower levels.
That's all we can do at the moment.
You think I will simply allow you to go?
How did I know this would happen?
And I'll help. I have a feeling I know how\nAudric here fights better than anyone.
Huh? How do you know that?
It doesn't look like there's time to discuss\nit. Are you sure?
Be safe, Chelle. And you, Valyx.
Go already! And take Sheila with you!
Jinlorda? Nedrick? Will you not withdraw?
This man is an impediment to my pact\nwith Bahamut and must be put down.
In that case, I am happy to do battle\nwith you, sir.
A fine strike, Father! Ah, but apologies.\nYou go by ＂Audric＂ now, yes?

You let Zethia go to the other world, and
you know that I am Aurelius, despite my
having cut my tie to the world. There can
only be one explanation for this...
Ah, but you always were clever.
What have you done to my son?
Your son? Ah, you mean the life that\nonce occupied this body.
He is dead. The wyrmscale took him.

He ever feared death. So much fear.
He spent his every moment gripped by it.
But then, he found in the Progenitor a
means to cheat the reaper of his due.
I must say, I never expected a child\nof humanity to break the seal.
When he died, I received his body.\nThough he is ＂dead,＂ his flesh lives on.\nI believe this would satisfy your son.
I quite like it, actually—this body, I mean.\nThe wyrmscale has made it hardier than\nyour normal human flesh sacks.
How tactless of you to interrupt a precious\nreunion between father and son.
This nonsense means nothing to me.\nYou die here, Progenitor.
And what can you do with only half of\nBahamut's power available, mmm?

You too are incomplete—because the
conditions for your revival have not yet
been met. Prudence dictates that I end
you before that time comes.
The world is full of clever children today,\nit seems.
As a reward, I will play with you.
Sacred Tree: Upper Strata\nAbove the Clouds
I hope Zethia and {player_name}\nand Gatov and everybody are okay...
We have no choice but to believe in them\nand continue on. Come.
He...he was our father. But why did he\nappear as he did?
I do not know the whole of his tale.
But whoever he is, our father is dead.\nThat is reality.
As well as the fact that our father's\nteachings live on in our hearts.
Let's move on. Not to alter the past,\nbut to change the future.
